I’m honored to be invited to join @TheSteveFund to talk about mental health in our community. Today, more than ever, we need to change the conversation to acknowledge what young people of color face and how we can all step up to support their mental health. 

It starts by sharing our stories. There is strength in sharing and in community. Wherever you are on your journey — you matter and so does your mental health. 

Find support at stevefund.org. The Steve Fund is the nation’s leading organization dedicated to supporting the mental health and emotional well-being of young people of color. #strengthinsharing
#youngpeopleofcolor
#mentalhealthawareness 
#mentalhealthmatters 
#theSteveFund

Closing out 2022, I just want to thank everyone who shared a part of this year with me.  Here’s some of my life highlights from this year. 
- released a record 
- performed my biggest and favorite shows to date 
- started my own business 
- Traveled the world doing what I love 
- Met and made great memories with some amazing people

Let’s envision what we want from 2023 and make it a reality.  Happy New Year! 🙏🏼🍾🎊

Excited to announce I’ll be performing on March 15th at the North Shore Music Theatre in Beverly, MA on March 15th! 

This show is very special to me. I’ve been working with a wonderful organization, called Express Yourself Inc., whose entire mission is to help give inner city youth a healthy outlet to express their emotions through the arts. Proceeds from this show will go to help fund Express Yourself Inc. so they can continue to do the great work they do! 

Please help in supporting them by grabbing your tickets today and coming out for an unforgettable night of friends and great music! I will have a full band performing hits and NEW MUSIC!
